# Commit Message Template

# Use conventional commits format:
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Type must be one of:
#   feat:     New feature
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation changes
#   style:    Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
#   refactor: Code refactoring
#   perf:     Performance improvements
#   test:     Adding or updating tests
#   build:    Build system changes
#   ci:       CI/CD changes
#   chore:    Other changes
#
# Scope (optional): backend, frontend, ui, api, websocket, store, docker, ci, docs
#
# Examples:
#   feat(backend): add user preferences API
#   fix(ui): resolve button alignment issue
#   docs(readme): update installation instructions
#   feat(api)!: change endpoint structure (BREAKING CHANGE)
#
# Use '!' after type/scope for breaking changes
# Keep subject line under 72 characters
# Use imperative mood: "add" not "added" or "adds"
#
# [Optional body - explain WHY, not what]
#
# [Optional footer - reference issues, breaking changes]
# Closes #123
# BREAKING CHANGE: description of breaking change

